        <p>We will retain your data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, or for such period as may be required for legal, accounting, audit, dispute-handling, or security purposes. If you provided data based on consent and later withdraw that consent, and we no longer have another lawful and necessary basis to retain it, we will, within a reasonable period, delete, de-identify, or stop processing/using your data.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>6. Whether You Must Provide Data</h2>
        <p>You are free to decide whether to provide personal data. However, if you choose not to provide certain necessary information, we may not be able to:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Complete survey pairing</li>
          <li>Contact you regarding free trials, in-depth interviews, or product tests</li>
          <li>Respond to your enquiry</li>
          <li>Provide certain functions or follow-up services</li>
        </ol>
        <p>If you are only browsing the website or completing survey sections that do not require contact information, the absence of contact data will generally not affect basic browsing or survey submission. However, if you wish to receive follow-up contact, trial invitations, or interview invitations, the relevant contact details will be required.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>7. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
        <p>To maintain normal website functionality, analyze traffic, understand survey sources, and improve user experience, we may use cookies or similar technologies. These technologies may help us record:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your device and browser information</li>
          <li>Page views and click behavior</li>
          <li>Survey entry and completion status</li>
          <li>Referral pages or recommendation links</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You may reject some or all cookies through your browser settings, but doing so may affect the operation of certain features.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>8. Third-Party Tools and Services</h2>
        <p>The website or research workflow may use the following third-party services. If any of these are not actually used, they may be removed from the final published version:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Google Forms / Google Workspace</strong> for survey collection, form processing, and data organization</li>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics / Search Console</strong> for website traffic analysis and performance monitoring</li>
          <li><strong>Notion / Airtable / spreadsheet tools</strong> for internal research organization and analysis</li>
          <li><strong>Email services</strong> for contacting respondents, sending trial invitations, scheduling interviews, or follow-up notifications</li>
          <li><strong>Cloud storage services</strong> for backup and storage of research data</li>
          <li><strong>Communication tools</strong> such as LINE, Zoom, or Google Meet for interviews, product testing, and follow-up communication</li>
        </ol>
        <p>These third-party services may process your data in accordance with their own privacy policies. We recommend that you review those policies as well.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>9. Data Security Measures</h2>
        <p>We will take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data, including where appropriate:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Access control and minimum-necessary access</li>
          <li>Password protection and, where applicable, two-factor authentication</li>
          <li>Separate management of pairing identifiers and contact information where feasible</li>
          <li>Avoiding unnecessary collection of sensitive data</li>
          <li>Preferring aggregated, summarized, or de-identified data when sharing externally</li>
          <li>Periodic review of whether retention remains necessary</li>
        </ol>
        <p>If personal data is stolen, leaked, altered, or otherwise compromised, we will take appropriate remedial action after investigation and, where appropriate, notify affected individuals in a suitable manner.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>10. De-identification and Research Analysis</h2>
        <p>Where feasible, we may de-identify, aggregate, or statistically process data for purposes such as:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Research analysis</li>
          <li>Insight generation</li>
          <li>Market validation</li>
          <li>Product design and improvement</li>
          <li>External explanation of overall research findings</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Once data has been processed so that specific individuals can no longer be directly or indirectly identified, it will generally no longer be treated as identifiable personal data.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>11. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Subject to applicable law, you may request in relation to your personal data:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Access or inspection</li>
          <li>A copy of your data</li>
          <li>Supplementation or correction</li>
          <li>Cessation of collection, processing, or use</li>
          <li>Deletion</li>
          <li>Withdrawal of consent previously given</li>
        </ol>
        <p>If you wish to exercise any of the rights above, please contact us using the details provided in this Policy. To protect data security, we may ask you to provide sufficient information to verify your identity. Where permitted by law, we may also request additional information to complete your request, or refuse all or part of a request where a legal exception applies.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>12. Minors or Other Representation Situations</h2>
        <p>If you do not have full legal capacity, or if consent or assistance must legally be given by a parent, guardian, supporter, or other authorized representative, please ask the appropriate representative to review this Policy with you and decide whether personal data should be provided. If we discover that additional consent or authorization is required, we may request supporting information or suspend further use of the data.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may revise this Privacy Policy from time to time due to changes in law, service adjustments, updates to research processes, or risk-control needs. The revised version will be published on this website and will take effect once published. If any revision materially affects your rights, we will take reasonable steps to draw your attention to it.</p>

        <hr />

